= Syntaq

Syntaq is a lightweight markup language based on (and backward compatible with)
Creole.

== Usage

From within Python:
``` python
from syntaq import Markup
print(Markup("hello, **world**").to_html())
```

== Inline Markup

|=    Style      |= Markup       |= HTML                    |=Example
|emphasis        |  ``//...//``  | ``<em>...</em>``         |This is //really// good.
|strong emphasis |  ``**...**``  | ``<strong>...</strong>`` |Do **not** do that!
|superscript     |  ``^^...^^``  | ``<sup>...</sup>``       |a^^2^^ = b^^2^^ + c^^2^^
|subscript       |  ``,,...,,``  | ``<sub>...</sub>``       |H,,2,,SO,,4,,
|quotation       |  ``""...""``  | ``<q>...</q>``           |""Live long and prosper"" -- Spock
|computer code   | ``~``...~```` | ``<code>...</code>``     |``print "hello, world"``
|link            | ``[[http://example.com/]]`` | ``<a href="http://example.com/">http://example.com/</a>``     |[[http://example.com/]]
|link with description
|image
|image link
|preformatted text

